 suppression of 5v5 expected goals against, teammate- and competition-adjusted. Higher means fewer chances allowed while he's on the ice."}, "ppOffense": {"receipts": [{"label": "Power-play xG impact (RAPM)", "value": "+0.00 xG/60", "tone": "neutral", "strong": true}, {"label": "PP ice time", "value": "3 min", "tone": "neutral"}], "summary": "His impact on the POWER PLAY \u2014 how much his team's chances improve with him on the man advantage, graded only against players who actually log power-play minutes (so a bottom-six grinder isn't penalized for never being out there).", "method": "Power-play expected-goals impact, RAPM-adjusted. Graded vs peers who actually play the PP."}, "pkDefense": {"receipts": [{"label": "Penalty-kill xG suppression (RAPM)", "value": "-0.27 xG/60", "tone": "neg", "strong": true}, {"label": "PK ice time", "value": "208 min", "tone": "neutral"}], "summary": "His impact on the PENALTY KILL \u2014 how well his team smothers chances while short-handed with him on the ice, graded against other penalty-killers.", "method": "Penalty-kill expected-goals suppression, RAPM-adjusted."}, "finishing": {"receipts": [{"label": "Career shots", "value": "1,331", "tone": "neutral"}, {"label": "Goals", "value": "70", "tone": "neutral"}, {"label": "Goals above expected", "value": "-22.0", "tone": "neg"}, {"label": "True talent / 100 shots", "value": "-1.19", "tone": "neg", "strong": true}, {"label": "Reliability", "value": "72%", "tone": "neutral"}], "summary": "Whether he scores MORE goals than the quality of his shots would predict \u2014 pure finishing talent. We take his goals minus the expected goals on every shot of his career, then trust it more the more he's shot (a 2,000-shot sample is real; a 200-shot hot streak isn't yet).", "method": "Goals minus expected over career shots, then regressed to the mean by sample size. A high-volume shooter earns a more confident read (higher reliability)."}}, "skills": {"hits60": {"receipts": [{"label": "Physicality